The '''1970 Ole Miss Rebels football team''' represented the [[University of Mississippi]] during the [[1970 college football season]] and in the [[1971 Gator Bowl (January)|1971 Gator Bowl]] against [[Auburn Tigers football|Auburn]] where Ole Miss lost 35â28. [[Archie Manning]] was the [[quarterback]] for Ole Miss.<ref>[http://www.gatorbowl.com/media_history_hb.html Gator Bowl Association: History]</ref> This also marked the last season of coach [[Johnny Vaught]]'s first tenure as the Ole Miss coach.
==Season== In the [[Egg Bowl]], [[Mississippi State Bulldogs football|Mississippi State]] beat Ole Miss by a score of 19â14. Ole Miss still held the lead in the series with 35 wins, 26 losses and 6 ties. In the [[Magnolia Bowl]], [[LSU Tigers football|LSU]] beat Ole Miss by a score of 61â17. LSU held the lead in the series with 30 wins, 26 losses, and 3 ties.
